<h1 id="nguá»“n-project-farmer-puppets">[NGUá»’N Project: FARMER PUPPETS]</h1>

<p>ğŸŒ¾ Seeing farmers working hard, doing arduous work in the vast paddy fields always gives NGUá»’N a feeling of familiarity and closeness. Today NGUá»’N will introduce you to farmer puppets as one of the most common elements of water puppet performances.</p>

<p>ğŸŒ¾ Farmer puppets are made from fig wood, jackfruit wood and have a height under 30cm with a â€œsmall waistâ€ of only 10cm. The unique point of these puppets is their simple costume, typical for farming but with vibrant colors such as red, yellow, and green. They also bring â€œproâ€ tool sets such as fishing rods, baskets to catch fish or healthy water buffaloes to plow the fields. It can be seen that, with its special sophistication, water puppetry has vividly recreated the idyllic life of the ancient Vietnamese.</p>

<p>ğŸ“ Have you noticed that even though agricultural life is a bit difficult, farmer puppets still give off a positive, fresh vibe? NGUá»’N believes that also represents the our nationâ€™s optimistic spirit despite lifeâ€™s ups and downs!</p>

<p>ğŸ“ Maybe you missed this: First settings of water puppet performances were paddy fields in the North Delta of Vietnam!</p>

